{"id": 7806, "source": "pestle", "subject": "chemistry", "course": null, "level": "SL", "paper": "1", "year": "2019", "session": "19M", "subtopic": "6-1-collision-theory-and-rates-of-reaction", "title": "19M.1.SL.TZ1.29", "topic_id": "6", "source_url": "https://pestle.pages.dev/app/", "question_html": "<div class=\"question\">\n<p><span style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\">The dotted line represents the formation of oxygen, O<sub>2</sub>(g), from the uncatalysed complete decomposition of hydrogen peroxide, H<sub>2</sub>O<sub>2</sub> (aq).</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\"><img height=\"324\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" width=\"438\"/></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\">Which curve represents a catalysed reaction under the same conditions?</span></span></p>\n</div>", "solution_html": "<div class=\"question\">\n<p>B</p>\n</div>", "examiners_html": "<div class=\"question\">\n<p>Graphical representation of catalysis was also well answered.</p>\n</div>"}